{
  "texts": [
    "The method takes into account permanent faults in the instruction cache, which degrade performance.",
    "The approach uses a static analysis to compute the worst-case execution path, ensuring the longest path is identified.",
    "It then calculates the probability of additional cache misses due to faulty cache blocks and derives a pWCET distribution.",
    "The method avoids exhaustive enumeration of all faulty cache configurations by using a probabilistic model based on the probability of cache block failures.",
    "Chen et al. [56] extend SPTA to handle both transient and permanent faults in random replacement caches using a Markov Chain model to capture the evolution of cache states and their probabilities.SPTA based on probabilities from random replacement caches focuses on the behavior of random replacement caches, which affect execution times due to varying access speeds."
  ]
}